The paper focuses on analyzing the robustness of Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) in the semantic space, particularly in the context of vision tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of different network architectures and proposes a formalized approach to detecting robust regions of DNNs, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of visualization techniques and optimization methods, which are commonly used in the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories, respectively. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CL, in that order.
